getQualifier

public java.lang.String getQualifier()
Gets the qualifier for this dependency.

A qualifier combined with the class helps identify the bean to inject. See canInject(Dependency) for details regarding qualifier rules.

Returns:
The qualifier.

canInject

public boolean canInject(Dependency bean)
Checks if the bean can be injected into this dependency.

Rules:

  • The bean must be of the same class or a superclass.
  • The qualifier must be identical, even if it's null.
  • Except if the class is an exact match and this qualifier is null.

Parameters:
bean - The bean to check.
Returns:
If the bean can be injected into this dependency.
